DIRECTIONS\
		\uc0\u8232 Step 1.     Rinse rice until the water runs clear; drain. \
\
Step 2.    Heat coconut oil and butter in a large skillet over medium-high heat. Cook and stir rice and coconut flakes for 3 to 4 minutes. \
\
\
Step 3.     Stir in the lime juice, then add the coconut milk, chicken broth, salt and lime zest. \
\
\
Step 4.   Bring to a low boil, then cover and reduce heat to low. Cook for 20 minutes. \
